ENTRY            E2826   20260224   20260508   20260508       E157
SUBENT        E2826001   20260224   20260508   20260508       E157
BIB                 12         25
TITLE      Discovery of proton-rich radioactive isotopes in the Z
           = 63-70 region produced by the projectile
           fragmentation of a 345-MeV/nucleon 238U beam
AUTHOR     (H.Suzuki, N.Fukuda, H.Takeda, Y.Shimizu, M.Yoshimoto,
            Y.Togano, H.Sato, N.Kitamura, S.Momota, K.Kusaka,
            Y.Yanagisawa, M.Ohtake, N.Fukunishi, S.Michimasa)
INSTITUTE  (2JPNIPC,2JPNTOK,2JPNKUT)
REFERENCE  (J,PTEP,2026,023D02,2026)
INC-SOURCE Beam intensity is about 60 particle-nA.
SAMPLE     - Chemical-form of target is element.
           - Physical-form of target is solid.
           - Target-thickness: 1 mm
METHOD     (TOFDE)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,2JPNIPC) RIBF
DETECTOR   (MAGSP,SCIN) BigRIPS
           (IOCH)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) Systematic uncertainty based on fluctuations
                   of cross sections for a single RI across
                   different settings, using the same method as
                   in previous studies.
           (ERR-S) Statistical uncertainty
STATUS     (TABLE,,H.Suzuki+,J,PTEP,2026,023D02,2026) Plotted in
                                                      Fig. 7
HISTORY    (20260223R) Received by e-mail from Dr. H. Suzuki.
           (20260224C) MA
ENDBIB              25
COMMON               2          3
EN         ERR-1
MEV/A      PER-CENT
 345.       20.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           32
SUBENT        E2826002   20260224   20260508   20260508       E157
BIB                  2          5
REACTION   (4-BE-9(92-U-238,X)ELEM/MASS,,SIG)
FLAG       (1.) 135Tb setting
           (2.) 146Yb setting
           (3.) 137Gd-W setting
           (4.) 137Gd-N setting
ENDBIB               5
